HEADWORD: Eubacteriales
<hw>Eubacteriales</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>one of two usually recognized
orders of true bacteria; gram-positive spherical or rod-shaped forms;
some are motile; in some classifications it is considered an order of
Schizomycetes.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> order Eubacteriales.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

